Troops of Operations Lafiya Dole has confirmed that four Boko haram terrorists were killed during their clearance operation in Konduga local government area of Borno state on Friday. A statement by Spokesman 7 Division Col. Ado Isa made available to new men in Maiduguri on Friday stated that gallant troops recovered four AK47 and ammunition. The statement reads: “Troops of 7 Division Nigerian Army in Operation Lafiya Dole based on credible information today conducted a clearance operation on suspected Boko Haram Terrorists (BHTs) hideout along Makinta Meleri in Konduga Local Government Area of Borno State. “During the operation, the gallant troops neutralised four  terrorists and recovered 4 AK-47 Rifles with registration numbers 58012289, 565240898 and 58006027, respectively. “They also recovered 3 Rifle Magazines containing 32 rounds of 7.62mm (Special) ammunition and 3 Bicycles.” While commending their gallantry, the Acting General Officer Commanding (GOC) 7 Division Nigerian Army and Commander Sector 1 Operation Lafiya Dole, Brig Gen Abdulmalik Bulama Biu charged the troops to sustain the tempo until the terrorists flushed out of their enclaves. “The Chief of Army Staff is proud of their doggedness and they should sustain the offensive until the BHTs are flushed out and total peace and security restored. “We wish to solicit for more information on suspected Boko Haram terrorists hideout.” The statement concluded.   Troops kill 7 insurgents in Borno Troops kill several insurgents in Borno JUST IN: Troops kill 2 Boko Haram insurgents, rescue 2 aged women in Borno